Obviously answer 3 is wrong. Damage to state property. If you violate, you will be fined with a large amount of money. Specifically: 
A fine of between VND 5,000,000 and 10,000,000 for one of the following violations:
 a) Illegally drilling, digging, cutting roads and sidewalks;
 b) Arbitrarily breaking the median strip, bridge mirror, works, traffic safety equipment on the road;
 c) Arbitrarily removing, opening and damaging manhole covers, manhole covers of underground works, tunnel systems on roads; d) Illegally blasting or exploiting soil, sand, gravel or stones, affecting road works.
